	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				<BR>
There is a way to pull the undead knight to the zone and do the quest, without help from others and without getting the keys to the Drelzna room.<BR>
It is rather risky though. I lost half of my life and was lucky to resist a fear spell. But I got the gauntlets.<BR>
<BR>
Here is how you do it. (I did it just now, at level 34).<BR>
<BR>
1) Go to outside the Drelzna room. Don't go into the right door (to Drelzna). Instead, go to the door straight head. (No key needed). At a specific corner (I forgot to get the /loc, silly me), you can cast sense the dead to target the undead knight.<BR>
<BR>
2) Summon a pet. When the undead knight is targeted, have the pet attack it. The pet will charge into the Drelzna room. With the undead knight targeted, you'll see it going form indifferently to threateningly.<BR>
<BR>
3) When your pet charges, run up the stairs a bit. I dont think you can run too far away because the knight won't follow then. I stayed in the stairs until the necros started casting on me (painful I might add). The undead night slashed me a few times for 80 points as well. <BR>
<BR>
4) Run to the zone. You'll need SoW or boots for this. Especially if the necros tag engulfing darkness on you (if so, have an egg shaped pumice ready). <BR>
<BR>
5) At the zone, cast feign death when you see the skeleton pets. hopefully the undead knight will be right after them. Given the feign death change, its likely that the undead knight will still attack you (66%) when you get up. Either zone or cast feign death another time. When you get up, hopefully the knight will be indifferent and very eager to help you solve the quest. Sort of feign pulling it, so to speak. I only noticed that the necro pets attacked me first, and the undead knight came right after. <BR>
<BR>
At higher levels, the necromancers in Drelznas room might not attack you, so you can pull the undead knight solo. Also, be careful if Drelzna is up. I assume she'll fire some nasty harmtouches which might put an end to the quest.<BR>
<BR>
The undead knight conned yellow and thus is level 35 or 36.<BR>
<BR>
Now, can anyone tell me where Melatite can be found? Off any clockwork? Or a specific gnome? Can it be bought with the right faction, and if so, how much does two melatite pieces cost?<BR>
<BR>
// Woland on Fennin Ro<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
